<p id="p11">This week, Brendon shares his surprising early impressions of the Ayn Odin Portal. Then Federico, Brendon and I dive into Nintendo Switch 2 pricing rumors, explore the performance issues of Assassin&rsquo;s Creed Shadows on M4 Macs despite being Steam Deck verified, and break down Qualcomm&rsquo;s confusing new G-series chips powering upcoming handhelds. Then, the trio reacts to OneXPlayer&rsquo;s chaotic ONEXSUGAR handheld and AYANEO&rsquo;s new devices. Plus, Federico has exciting news about a DLSS plugin for Steam Deck that improves performance on games like Final Fantasy VII Rebirth, turning blurry gameplay into a sharp, high-settings experience.</p>
<hr id="hr12"><h2 id="npc-xl">NPC XL</h2>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img src="https://cdn.macstories.net/qeoq9xysm7w-hd-1741814580073.jpg" alt=""><p class="image-caption"></p></div>
<p id="p14">This week on NPC XL, Federico, Brandon and I share their most unusual handheld gaming devices. From my nostalgic Tamagotchi Connection to Brandon&rsquo;s beast of a modded PSP Go and Federico&rsquo;s Ashida Wii, the conversation reveals their weird obsessions with handheld gaming.</p>
